		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati Ohio</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>23 February 1848</date></p>
			<p>Rev Sir</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)">I received in due course your favor of<lb/> the 14th Inst.&#58;  I perceived the notice taken of the Retrospects<lb/> in the <date>February</date> number of the Occident&#44; and now hand<lb/> you a circular containing notices of the work by the Press here<lb/> which please insert at large in your April number of the<lb/> Occident&#44; and send your amount for the same to <persName>Messieurs<lb/> Robinson</persName> and <persName>Jones</persName> of this City.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Mr Guthrie</persName>&#44; the partner of <persName>Mr. Elias Mayer</persName><lb/> has kindly taken charge of this and of 50 Copies of the<lb/> Retrospect&#58; I feel obliged by your pronure[&#63;] to bring them<lb/> under the notice of your friends and shall be glad to see<lb/> the work received in the Occident</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)">I need not tell you who must have had<lb/> sufficient experience of the fact&#44; how much exertion must be<lb/> used to preserve from loss there who engage in similar efforts<lb/> as these on behalf of our people&#58; As yet I am minus 2/3 d.<lb/> the cost of printing the Retrospect but through the influence<lb/> of Gentlemen like yourself I trust I shall not be a sufferer<lb/> to any extent in the end&#58; I have not sought to make money<lb/> through this channel but I confess my inability to sustain<lb/> <sic>conviniently</sic> any loss from it.  I wrote <persName>Rabbi Lilienthall</persName><lb/> and the <persName>Revd Aurel Leo</persName> but as yet have not been favored<lb/> with any reply&#8212;I am reverend Sir</p>
		  <p rend="indent(3)">Your obt. Servant</p>
		  <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">A A Lindo</persName></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee>&#8211;</p>

		<pb n="2"/>
		
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>Favored by</p>
			<p><persName>Mr. A. A. Guthrie</persName>	<placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		  
